The geo data is maintained in a Postgres database table. Postgres has excellent geographical options when the PostGIS extension is installed.

In order to create a dump, issue the following statements:

UPDATE bp_areas
SET geojson = CAST(ST_AsGeoJSON(ST_MakeValid(ST_RemoveRepeatedPoints(ST_GeomFromGeoJSON(ST_AsGeoJSON(the_geom,9))))) AS JSON);

The data can be exported using the following query, wrapped in a COPY () TO STDOUT WITH CSV HEADER statement:

SELECT 
	gid, 
	CASE 
		WHEN 
			type = 'Nature' 
		THEN 
			CONCAT(locality, ' (',  source, ')') 
		ELSE
			locality 
	END 
		AS locality,
	geojson,
	iso,
	source,
	type,
	locality_nl
FROM bp_areas;

Alternatively, the database can be loaded in PgAdmin 4. Use the bp_areas.tar file in this repo to load the data.
